# Files to hide from implementer-role subagents.
#
# Honored by some Claude tooling and IDE plugins. Behavior is not uniform across
# every Claude entry point — treat this as belt-and-suspenders. The primary
# control is the dispatch prompt that defines an "implementer" role; this file
# is the structural backup.
#
# WHY: When an implementer subagent can read both the spec AND the test file,
# the cheapest way to make the test pass is often to weaken the test. Hiding
# tests forces the implementer to work from the spec alone — the test then
# becomes an independent verifier instead of a target to defeat.
#
# A "writer/reviewer/observer" agent that needs to see tests should override
# this by reading the file with an absolute path (.claudeignore filters
# globbing/search context, not direct Reads).

src/**/__tests__/
src/**/*.test.ts
src/**/*.test.tsx
src/**/*.spec.ts
backend/**/*.test.ts

# Test infrastructure that, if visible, lets an implementer reverse-engineer
# what the tests stub. Implementers should depend on the real API contract.
src/__tests__/setup.ts
src/__tests__/helpers/
